translated: Högsell, Tore Axel Emanuel, lawyer, Kalmar, born December 25, 1901 in Madesjö, Kalmar county, son of district fishery officer Axel H. and Tora Forsell. Married in 1929 to Edith Jönsson. Children: Åke born in 1935 and Britta born in 1939. He graduated from high school in 1920 and earned a degree in law in 1926. He worked as a clerk at the Court of Appeals and as an assistant judge in East army district court from 1926 to 1929, including three months as a judge. He opened Tore Högsell's law firm in Nybro from 1929 to 1935, and after that, he worked for the Life Insurance Company Thule from 1934 to 1944. He then owned Tore Högsell's law firm in Kalmar from 1944. He was a member of the Swedish Bar Association and the city council in Nybro, and he was the auditor of the town accounts and chairman of the building board. He was also a member of the pension committee, and more. From 1930 to 1934, he was the chairman of the board for Kalmar archipelago shipping company AB. He was the secretary and treasurer for the association of voluntary military officers in Kalmar, and he was the chairman of the board for the Lilla Society in Kalmar. He was the president of the Rotary Club, and more. He enjoyed gardening, motorcycling, and various sports. He passed away 1970 in Kalmar.
